This paper discusses the relationship between interpretability and adversarial robustness in deep neural networks. As such, it is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories within computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), computer security and cryptography (cs.CR), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
